[thinking] I'm thinking about how the Groovy-based library classes that implement GroovyObject are part of the public binary, even if the class is internal. I wonder if I could include this in a test to cover it, but then I'm concerned that it might violate the principle of covering supported behavior only through the library's normal public API. It's a tricky situation, and I want to make sure I'm adhering to the guidelines correctly!
[thinking] 
